FBIS3-51462 "drlat011_a_94010" FBIS-LAT-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 CARIBBEAN More on Raul Castro Remarks to Reporters FL1501022694 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in Spanish 0100 GMT 15 Jan 94 FL1501022694 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] As announced, we now feature the statement Army General Raul Castro made to reporters following the ceremony marking the beginning of the Central Army defense training year in Cienfuegos. [Begin recording] Despite the special situation the country has been enduring for several years and which you know about, in the last three years -- to speak in concrete terms -- the Revolutionary Armed Forces, the Interior Ministry, and the entire gigantic force of militiamen, [words indistinct] the great army of the people which will be the ones conducting the doctrine of the war of the entire people are aware....[changes thought] Despite this, I repeat, everything we do despite the situation, all the sacrifices, and our limited resources, we continue to develop -- from the people's tunnels to the medium and large tunnels, which are part of the preparation of the theater of military operations, part of the entire gigantic effort by our people. All this has grown despite this situation, and there is one single goal: To prepare for war precisely in order to avoid war, which is our dearest hope. Once we said in a meeting that the most beautiful battle or the greatest victory our people can attain is precisely avoiding war, which for us -- we have said this before -- is the same as to have won it. [end recording]
